An alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews. Event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards at the entrance, while human resources teams jot notes on tablets as students introduce themselves, and career counselors remind attendees to maintain eye contact. Students are also using tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database. A whiteboard lists employers who are scheduling same-day interviews, and a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit. Additionally, workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom.

Career counselors remind attendees to maintain eye contact. As the event progresses, announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair.
